  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "(*Phase 1 summary / milestone report. The BRACKET-level pole-cancellation statement closes\nEXACTLY and symmetrically for both sites (proven to literal 0 residual on symbolic monomial and\ntwisted-monomial test bases, and numerically to 0 on the actual Q1 Baxter functions, all 41 states\nof the full rep sweep, both directions). The ROTATION/functional-CG-overlap dictionary, however,\ndoes NOT mirror symmetrically: det1s2[λ2][k^(u/h)Q1] fails to reproduce the site-2-rotated overlap\nOPg2 under any state-independent rescaling φ(k)=α k, except at the two extremal weight sectors\nM=0 and M=λ1+λ2 (where α=-1, matching site 1's value exactly). Interior weight sectors give\ngenuinely state-dependent ratios (verified on two independent λ2=1 reps, (2,1) and (3,1), same\nqualitative pattern both times) — this is a real structural asymmetry between the two sites in\nthis companion-twist SoV gauge (T(u)=L1(u).L2(u) singles out site 1 as the first/distinguished\nfactor in the monodromy product), not a bug: Q1(u)=κ1^(u/h)q_n(u) is pinned to κ1, the twist\neigenvalue naturally associated with the transfer-matrix asymptotics/SoV covector construction\nbuilt starting from site 1 (Section E's xL1/t1 hierarchy has no site-2 analogue proven in this\nnotebook), so there is no a priori reason a NAIVE site-2 mirror using the same Q1 and the same\nkind of measure should close the way the site-1 one does. The required milestone check (test it)\nhas been carried out and is DIAGNOSED AS FAILING for generic states; Phase 2 is attempted next\nusing the well-established site-1 dictionary as an anchor, and this asymmetry is expected to\nresurface there.*)",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "(*Section H — Phase 2: two independent local rotations. Brute-force operatorial target\nO[k1,k2] := (⟨x0[λ1]|exp[-k1 E21^(1)]⊗⟨x0[λ2]|exp[-k2 E21^(2)]).Psi[λ1,λ2][M,n], using\ngenNontrivial={2,1} (E21) on BOTH sites (confirmed the nontrivial generator on both, Cells 69/89).\nSearch for a functional-side FSoV determinant reproducing this exactly. Constraints: at k2=0 must\nequal FLdet[λ1,λ2][M,n][k1]=det1[λ1][k1^(u/h)Q1] (Section F, established exact); at k1=0 must equal\nthe site-2 analogue — but Phase 1 found the naive analogue (FLdet2/OPg2 under φ=αk) does NOT close\nfor generic states, so this joint construction is tested with that caveat in mind.*)",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(*O[λ1,λ2][M,n][k1,k2]: the brute-force two-parameter operatorial overlap.*)\nClearAll[O2rot];\nO2rot[λ1_,λ2_][M_,n_][k1_,k2_] := Flatten[KroneckerProduct[\n   xSingle[λ1][{0}].gRot[λ1][2,1][-k1],\n   xSingle[λ2][{0}].gRot[λ2][2,1][-k2]\n ]] . Psi[λ1,λ2][M,n];\n(*sanity: k2->0 must reproduce the known site-1 dictionary FLdet exactly, k1->0 the site-2 analogue.*)\ntestState = {1,0}; testRep = {2,1};\nchk1 = Simplify[(O2rot[testRep[[1]],testRep[[2]]][testState[[1]],testState[[2]]][k1,0]) - FLdet[testRep[[1]],testRep[[2]]][testState[[1]],testState[[2]]][k1]];\nchk2 = Simplify[(O2rot[testRep[[1]],testRep[[2]]][testState[[1]],testState[[2]]][0,k2]) - FLdet2[testRep[[1]],testRep[[2]]][testState[[1]],testState[[2]]][k2]];\n{\"O[k1,0]-FLdet[k1] (must be 0)\", Chop[N[chk1],10^-15], \"O[0,k2]-FLdet2[k2] (expected NONZERO per Phase1 finding)\", Chop[N[chk2],10^-15]}",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
       "data": "<div class=\"wl-output-block\"><div class=\"wl-output-header\" style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;width:100%;min-height:22px;\" data-session-epoch=\"941596\" data-output-id=\"1058\" data-out-n=\"311\" data-sub-idx=\"7\" data-output-format=\"WLLatex\" data-output-is-graphics=\"0\" data-cell-idx=\"95\" data-sub-start=\"10\" data-sub-end=\"10\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;color:#888;margin-right:8px;\">Out[311]=</span></div><div class=\"wl-output-content\"><div class=\"vscode-wolfram-wllatex-prerendered wl-lb-pending\" data-lb-id=\"lb-mrqpz6gh-j4ptmfw\" data-page-width-em=\"21\" data-latex-b64=\"XGxlZnRce1x0ZXh0e09bazEsMF0tRkxkZXRbazFdIChtdXN0IGJlIDApfSwwLFx0ZXh0e09bMCxrMl0tRkxkZXQyW2syXSAoZXhwZWN0ZWQgTk9OWkVSTyBwZXIgUGhhc2UxIGZpbmRpbmcpfSxcbGVmdCgtMy4wNzE5NzU2NDIxMDUwNzU1LTAuNTE3MjE2NTM3MTcwNTIyNVwsXG1hdGhybXtpfVxyaWdodClcLGsyXHJpZ2h0XH0=\" style=\"opacity:0.65;transition:opacity 0.35s\"><div class=\"wl-lb-content\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">{</span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">O[k1,0]-FLdet[k1] (must be 0)</span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">O[0,k2]-FLdet2[k2] (expected NONZERO per Phase1 finding)</span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">−</span><span class=\"mord\">3.0719756421050755</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">−</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0.5172165371705225</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathrm\">i</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">)</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"mord\">2</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">}</span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div></div></div>",
       "mime": "x-application/wolfram-language-html"
      },
      {
       "data": "Out[311]= \\left\\{\\text{O[k1,0]-FLdet[k1] (must be 0)},0,\\text{O[0,k2]-FLdet2[k2] (expected NONZERO per Phase1 finding)},\\left(-3.0719756421050755-0.5172165371705225\\,\\mathrm{i}\\right)\\,k2\\right\\}",
       "mime": "text/plain"
      }
     ],
     "id": "5b4e3681-50b2-4126-a3b1-36160c75f804"
    }
