  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "(*Phase 2 outcome — OBSTRUCTION, reported precisely rather than forced further.\n\nTarget: O[λ1,λ2][M,n][k1,k2] = (⟨x0[λ1]|exp[-k1 E21^(1)]⊗⟨x0[λ2]|exp[-k2 E21^(2)]).Psi[λ1,λ2][M,n]\n(built as O2rot, Cell 97). Structural fact established first (Cell 99): O2rot does NOT factorize as\na product of its two 1-parameter slices, O[k1,k2] != O[k1,0]*O[0,k2] — genuine k1^2 k2 and k1 k2\ncross terms are present, i.e. the rotated eigenstate is genuinely entangled across the two tensor\nfactors, so no pure-product ansatz F(k1)G(k2) can work.\n\nTwo natural 2x2-determinant candidates were built and tested against the full O2rot, both using the\nestablished row structure {br[λ1,λ2][1][g],br[λ1,λ2][1][ug]} / {br[λ1,λ2][2][g],br[λ1,λ2][2][ug]}\nwith the overall 1/(g1(θ1)g2(θ2)(θ2-θ1)) normalization pattern of Section C's det[λ1,λ2][f]:\n  - Candidate 1 (Fcand1, Cell 98): row-1 uses g1=P1site2[λ2][u]k1^(u/h)Q1[u] (Phase-1 pole-cancelling\n    insertion), row-2 uses g2=P2site1[λ1][u]k2^(u/h)Q1[u].\n  - Candidate 2 (Fcand2, Cell 101): same but WITHOUT the P-insertions (bare g1=k1^(u/h)Q1,\n    g2=k2^(u/h)Q1).\nBOTH fail comprehensively: coefficient-by-coefficient comparison (Cell 100) shows only the trivial\nk1^0 k2^0 term agrees (=1, matching O2rot(0,0)=1 by normalization); every other monomial in k1,k2\nhas an O(1) mismatch, not merely a wrong overall constant. Sharpest diagnostic (Cells 104-105):\neven the boundary slice Fcand1(k1,0) is NOT simply proportional to the known-correct FLdet[k1] —\nthe constant (k1^0) coefficients agree (ratio 1, consistent with Phase 1's C1pred/P1site2[λ2][θ1]=1\nfor this rep) but the k1^1 coefficients' ratio is ≈6.25, a totally different value, showing the\nmismatch is a genuine SHAPE failure, not a fixable normalization. This traces to the determinant\nstructure itself: Det[{{a,b},{c,d}}]=ad-bc mixes row 2 into row 1's apparent k2->0 limit through the\nshared 1/(g2(θ2)) normalization in a way that does not simply \"turn off\" row 2's contribution — the\nnaive expectation that Fcand(k1,0) collapses to the single-row object br[1][P1site2 g1]/g1(θ1)\n(which DOES work, per Phase 1 Test 3) does not carry over once a second row is adjoined into a\ngenuine 2x2 determinant.\n\nROOT CAUSE (traced to the Phase-1 required milestone, Cells 88-95): the single-parameter site-2\nmirror det1s2[λ2][k^(u/h)Q1] itself already fails to reproduce OPg2 under any state-independent\nrescaling φ(k)=αk for interior weight sectors (only the two extremal M=0,λ1+λ2 sectors close, with\nthe SAME α=-1 as site 1). Since even that simpler 1-parameter problem is unsolved, no 2-parameter\njoint object built from it should have been expected to close either — Candidates 1-2's total\nfailure is consistent with, not independent of, that earlier finding.\n\nWHAT WOULD BE NEEDED: a genuinely different single-site-2 functional object (not the naive\nθ2-centered mirror of Nn1/mu1/br1) that correctly reproduces OPg2 for interior states — plausibly\ntied to Section D's left eigenvector Psi_Left/braket construction (the only other machinery in this\nnotebook independently verified to reproduce the genuine 2-site pairing, via braket=det[Q,Q]) rather\nthan a naive copy of Section F's site-1 recipe. This is flagged as the natural next step, not\npursued further here per the \"stop and report\" instruction once systematic candidates failed.*)",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "(*Section I — Phase 2 attempt via the GRADED EXPANSION route. The site-2 rotation is a FINITE sum\n(gRot truncates at m=λ2): ⟨x0[λ2]|exp[-k2 E21] = Σ_{m=0}^{λ2} (-k2)^m/m! ⟨x0[λ2]|E21^m, so\nO[k1,k2] = Σ_m (-k2)^m/m! O_m[k1] with O_m[k1] := (⟨x0[λ1]|exp[-k1E21]⊗⟨x0[λ2]|E21^m).Psi.\nConjecture: each graded piece has a determinant/bracket form with the PARTIAL pole-cancelling\ninsertion Pm[u]:=Product[(u-θ2-hk),{k,0,m-1}] (empty product=1 at m=0), which kills tower-2 lattice\npoints 0..m-1 and should select the s2=m slice. Ordered gated steps 0-4 below, each a prerequisite\nfor the next; report precisely at whichever step fails rather than forcing further.*)",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(*STEP 0 — baseline anchor: does the GLOBAL 2-site det (Section C's det[λ1,λ2][f], same twist\n  inserted at BOTH nodes since f carries a single k) equal O[k,k] (same k at both sites)? This\n  calibrates conventions/normalizations before attempting the graded decomposition.*)\nClearAll[step0Report];\nstep0Report = {};\nDo[\n  {λ1,λ2} = rep;\n  Do[\n    fFun[uu_] := k^(uu/h) Q1[λ1,λ2][st[[1]],st[[2]]][uu];\n    dGlobal = Simplify[det[λ1,λ2][fFun[u]]];\n    oDiag = Simplify[O2rot[λ1,λ2][st[[1]],st[[2]]][k,k]];\n    resid = Chop[N[dGlobal-oDiag]/.k->N[7/3+I/5],10^-12];\n    ratio = Chop[N[Simplify[dGlobal/oDiag]]/.k->N[7/3+I/5],10^-12];\n    AppendTo[step0Report,{λ1,λ2,st,resid,ratio}]\n  ,{st,statesOf[λ1,λ2]}]\n,{rep,{{1,1},{2,1},{1,2}}}];\nworstStep0 = Max[Abs[step0Report[[All,4]]]];\n{\"STEP 0: det[λ1,λ2][k^(u/h)Q1] vs O[k,k], worst |residual| (sample k)\", worstStep0,\n \"sample rows {λ1,λ2,state,resid,ratio}\", Take[step0Report, UpTo[6]]}",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
       "data": "<div class=\"wl-output-block\"><div class=\"wl-output-header\" style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;width:100%;min-height:22px;\" data-session-epoch=\"941596\" data-output-id=\"1067\" data-out-n=\"348\" data-sub-idx=\"5\" data-output-format=\"WLLatex\" data-output-is-graphics=\"0\" data-cell-idx=\"106\" data-sub-start=\"17\" data-sub-end=\"18\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;color:#888;margin-right:8px;\">Out[348]=</span></div><div class=\"wl-output-content\"><div class=\"vscode-wolfram-wllatex-prerendered wl-lb-pending\" data-lb-id=\"lb-mrqpzaj8-jl2x73h\" data-page-width-em=\"21\" data-latex-b64=\"\" style=\"opacity:0.65;transition:opacity 0.35s\"><div class=\"wl-lb-content\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:7.2001em;vertical-align:-3.35em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen\"><span class=\"delimsizing mult\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:3.85em;\"><span style=\"top:-1.366em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3.816em;\"></span><span class=\"delimsizinginner delim-size4\"><span>⎩</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-1.358em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3.816em;\"></span><span style=\"height:1.816em;width:0.8889em;\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"0.8889em\" height=\"1.816em\" style=\"width:0.8889em\" viewBox=\"0 0 888.89 1816\" preserveAspectRatio=\"xMinYMin\"><path d=\"M384 0 H504 V1816 H384z M384 0 H504 V1816 H384z\"/></svg></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.816em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3.816em;\"></span><span class=\"delimsizinginner delim-size4\"><span>⎨</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-4.958em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3.816em;\"></span><span style=\"height:1.816em;width:0.8889em;\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"0.8889em\" height=\"1.816e