  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(*A restricted to a level-L block is UPPER TRIANGULAR (in s1 ascending order) — x2[{s1,m}] only\n  involves basis vectors with s1'>=s1. Invert and inspect (Wolfram handles small triangular inverses\n  cleanly).*)\nblk32inv = Simplify[Inverse[blk32]];\nblk32inv // MatrixForm",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
