   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "(*Section K final report — the two-rotation construction CLOSES completely, derivation-first.\n\nSTEP 1 — Paul's corrected wave-function factorization CONFIRMED EXACTLY:\n  x2[λ1,λ2][{s1,s2}].Psi[M,n] = Q1(θ1+s1h)·Q1(θ2+s2h) / (Q1(θ1)·Q1(θ2))\nusing Q1 WITH its own κ1^(u/h) twist prefactor (Q1 exactly as defined in Section B) — literal 0\nresidual over 297 cases (41 states × every (s1,s2), Cell 140). The prefactor does NOT cancel to 1:\nanalytically Q1(θ1+s1)/Q1(θ1)=κ1^s1·q_n(θ1+s1)/q_n(θ1) (h=1), so the ratio genuinely carries an\noverall κ1^(s1+s2) factor; the bare-polynomial (no-prefactor) version was checked and fails with a\nlarge nonzero residual (3.74, Cell 141), confirming the prefactor is essential, not incidental.\n\nSTEP 2 — B solved by pure linear algebra (no guessing): MP[a,b][state]:=(xL1[λ1][{a}]⊗xL1[λ2][{b}]).Psi[state]\nexpanded in the W[s,t]:=x2[{s,t}].Psi basis with level support s+t=a+b, using EVERY state of a rep as\none equation (massively overdetermined) — LeastSquares gives residual 0 (machine-zero, ~10^-24) in\nevery case tried (37 (rep,a,b) cases, Cell 144). KEY STRUCTURAL FACT (Cell 145, exact match): B IS\nLITERALLY THE MATRIX INVERSE OF SECTION J's A, block-by-block — MP=B.W and x2=A.(xL1⊗xL1) are simply\ninverse changes of basis. This gives B's DIAGONAL in closed form for free (reciprocal of Section J's\nboxed formula):\n  B[a,b;a,b] = Pochhammer[λ1+θ12-b+1,b] / Pochhammer[a+θ12-b+1,b],   θ12=θ1-θ2, h=1\nB is REP-INDEPENDENT in the same sense A was: B[a,b;s,t] depends only on λ1 (not λ2) — verified by\ncomparing (2,1) vs (2,2) vs (1,2) vs (1,3): identical values wherever both reps admit the same entry\n(Cell 144's table). The off-diagonal closed form was not derived analytically (same difficulty as\nA's off-diagonal in Section J — a genuine Hahn/Racah-type structure) but is fully accessible\nnumerically/exactly via LeastSquares+Rationalize for any (λ1,λ2,a,b), which is what Steps 3-4 use.\n\nSTEP 3 — ASSEMBLY CLOSES EXACTLY (the actual payoff): O[k1,k2] = Σ_{a,b} cA[a](k1)cB[b](k2)·MP[a,b],\ncA[a](k1)=(-k1)^a/a!·γ_a(λ1), cB[b](k2)=(-k2)^b/b!·γ_b(λ2), with MP expanded via B and W as above —\nhard-verified to LITERAL 0 residual across the FULL 41-state, 6-rep sweep on 2 independent (k1,k2)\ngrid points each (82 cases total, Cell 151), directly against the independently-defined O2rot. THE\nTWO-ROTATION FORMULA IS NOW FULLY ESTABLISHED as a genuine Q-bilinear functional identity.\n\nSTEP 4 — the TRUE sum rule, DERIVED (not guessed) by expanding det[λ1,λ2][k^(u/h)Q1]'s residue sums\nexplicitly (mu's poles are simple, so each residue is just a pointwise evaluation — no derivatives):\n  det[λ1,λ2][k^(u/h)Q1] = Σ_{s,t} w1(s)w2(t)(θ2-θ1+(t-s)h)/(θ2-θ1)·k^(s+t)·W[s,t]\n(verified exactly against the live det[...] object, Cell 147: residual literal 0). Equating this to\nStep 3's assembly at k1=k2=k, term-by-term in k^L·W[s,t], gives:\n  (-1)^(s+t) Σ_{a+b=s+t} γ_a(λ1)γ_b(λ2)/(a!b!)·B[a,b;s,t] = w1(s)w2(t)(θ2-θ1+(t-s)h)/(θ2-θ1)\nhard-verified to literal 0 deviation across 20 (λ1,λ2,s,t) cases (Cell 148) — the genuine, correctly\nderived replacement for Section J's failed conjectured sum rule.\n\nSTEP 5 (timeboxed) — the naive per-row-insertion determinant Fcand[k1,k2] (Section H's Candidate 2,\nno P-insertion) was expanded via the SAME residue mechanism as Step 4 and found EXACTLY:\n  Fcand[k1,k2] = Σ_{s,t} R[s,t]·k1^s k2^t·W[s,t],   R[s,t]:=w1(s)w2(t)(θ2-θ1+(t-s)h)/(θ2-θ1)\ni.e. its k1^a k2^b coefficient is the SINGLE \"diagonal\" term R[a,b]W[a,b] — no recoupling. The\nCORRECT O[k1,k2]'s k1^a k2^b coefficient is instead (-1)^(a+b)/(a!b!)γ_a(λ1)γ_b(λ2)Σ_{s+t=a+b}B[a,b;s,t]W[s,t],\na genuine LINEAR COMBINATION over the full level-(a+b) recoupling row of B — this is EXACTLY why\nSection H's naive candidates all failed (they implicitly assumed the diagonal-only relationship\nFcand encodes). The difference matrix Diff[a,b;s,t]:=[(-1)^(a+b)/(a!b!)γ_aγ_b B[a,b;s,t]]-δ_{s,a}δ_{t,b}R[a,b]\nis nonzero for every (a,b)≠(0,0) (Cell 153) — it is NOT a simple polynomial-dressing correction to\nFcand; it is the genuine B-recoupling itself, i.e. the difference IS the physics Section J's A/B\nmachinery captures, not a small perturbative correction on top of a naive determinant. This is the\nprecise, derived answer to \"what does the naive candidate miss.\"\n\nBOTTOM LINE: the two-independent-local-rotation formula O[k1,k2] is now a FULLY CLOSED, hard-verified\nQ-bilinear identity (Step 3), built from the exact wave-function factorization (Step 1), the\nexactly-solved (diagonal-closed-form, rep-independent) recoupling matrix B=A^{-1} (Step 2), and a\nproperly DERIVED sum rule (Step 4) replacing Section J's failed guess. Open for a future session:\nB's off-diagonal closed form (equivalent difficulty to A's, not attempted further here) and whether\nthe Hahn/Racah-polynomial identification can be made explicit analytically.*)",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "(*Section L — Paul's directed ansatz: does O[k1,k2] admit a 2x2-determinant form with row 1\nbuilt purely from site-1 lattice values Q1(θ1+sh) and row 2 purely from site-2 lattice values\nQ1(θ2+rh)? Decidable from Section K: O[k1,k2] = Σ_{s,t} M[s,t](k1,k2) W[s,t], M[s,t](k1,k2) :=\nΣ_{a+b=s+t} cA[a](k1)cB[b](k2) B[a,b;s,t] (exact rationals). The ansatz det = u1(k1)^T v2(k2) −\nu2(k1)^T v1(k2) means M(k1,k2), as a (λ1+1)x(λ2+1) matrix, must be RANK <=2 for every (k1,k2), with\nrow/column spaces independent of the other variable. GATE 1 (pointwise rank) below; GATE 2\n(separated dependence) and extraction follow only if Gate 1 passes.*)",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(*Build M[s,t](k1,k2) as a (λ1+1)x(λ2+1) matrix, exact rational entries at rational (k1,k2).\n  Reuses Section K's solveBratM (exact B) and gammaFun (γ_a(λ)=λ!/(λ-a)!).*)\nClearAll[Mmatrix];\nMmatrix[λ1_,λ2_][k1_,k2_] := Table[\n  Module[{L=s+t, aMin, aMax},\n    aMin = Max[0,L-λ2]; aMax = Min[L,λ1];\n    Sum[\n      Module[{srng,bv,idx},\n        {srng,bv} = solveBratM[λ1,λ2][a,L-a][[1;;2]];\n        idx = FirstPosition[srng,s];\n        If[idx===Missing[\"NotFound\"], 0,\n          (-k1)^a/a! gammaFun[λ1,a] (-k2)^(L-a)/(L-a)! gammaFun[λ2,L-a] bv[[idx[[1]]]]]\n      ]\n    ,{a,aMin,aMax}]\n  ]\n,{s,0,λ1},{t,0,λ2}];\n(*smoke test: rep (2,1) at a generic rational (k1,k2) point.*)\nMtest21 = Mmatrix[2,1][7/3,5/2];\n{\"M matrix (rep (2,1), k1=7/3,k2=5/2)\", Mtest21 // MatrixForm, \"MatrixRank\", MatrixRank[Mtest21]}",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
       "data": "<div class=\"wl-output-block\"><div class=\"wl-output-header\" style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;width:100%;min-height:22px;\" data-session-epoch=\"941596\" data-output-id=\"1104\" data-out-n=\"561\" data-sub-idx=\"5\" data-output-format=\"WLLatex\" data-output-is-graphics=\"0\" data-cell-idx=\"155\" data-sub-start=\"18\" data-sub-end=\"18\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;color:#888;margin-right:8px;\">Out[561]=</span></div><div class=\"wl-output-content\"><div class=\"vscode-wolfram-wllatex-prerendered wl-lb-pending\" data-lb-id=\"lb-mrqq07rp-d4x7il1\" data-page-width-em=\"21\" data-latex-b64=\"XGxlZnRce1x0ZXh0e00gbWF0cml4IChyZXAgKDIsMSksIGsxPTcvMyxrMj01LzIpfSxcYmVnaW57cG1hdHJpeH0xICYgLVxmcmFjezExNX17NH1cXFxmcmFjezI1OX17MTJ9ICYgXGZyYWN7MzIyfXsxNX1cXC1cZnJhY3sxOTZ9ezQ1fSAmIC1cZnJhY3syNDV9ezE4fVxlbmR7cG1hdHJpeH0sXHRleHR7TWF0cml4UmFua30sMlxyaWdodFx9\" style=\"opacity:0.65;transition:opacity 0.35s\"><div class=\"wl-lb-content\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:3.6153em;vertical-align:-1.5577em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen\"><span class=\"delimsizing mult\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:2.05em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3.15em;\"></span><span class=\"delimsizinginner delim-size4\"><span>⎩</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-2.492em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3.15em;\"></span><span style=\"height:0.016em;width:0.8889em;\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"0.8889em\" height=\"0.016em\" style=\"width:0.8889em\" viewBox=\"0 0 888.89 16\" preserveAspectRatio=\"xMinYMin\"><path d=\"M384 0 H504 V16 H384z M384 0 H504 V16 H384z\"/></svg></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.15em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3.15em;\"></span><span class=\"delimsizinginner delim