  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(*Confirm rank 3 is GENERIC (not an artifact of the 4 sample points) by computing Det[Mmatrix]\n  as a SYMBOLIC polynomial in k1,k2 for rep (2,2) — if identically 0, rank<=2 almost everywhere\n  despite the isolated nonzero samples (impossible for a low-degree polynomial nonzero at 4 points,\n  but verify directly for full rigor) and cross-validate the M-reconstruction against O2rot on this\n  symbolic det computation.*)\ndetM22sym = Det[Mmatrix[2,2][k1,k2]] // Simplify;\n{\"Det[M(k1,k2)] symbolic, rep (2,2)\", detM22sym, \"identically zero?\", detM22sym === 0}",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
