  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "(*Section L final report — GATE 1 (pointwise rank) FAILS. Per the ask-first protocol (\"if a gate\nfails, stop and report rather than invent alternatives\"), Gate 2 and the extraction step were NOT\nattempted; this is the complete, decisive answer to Paul's ansatz as posed.\n\nTHE ANSATZ, restated: O[k1,k2] equals a normalization times a 2x2 determinant with row 1 built\npurely from site-1 lattice values {Q1(θ1+sh)}_{s=0}^{λ1} (coefficients depending on λ1,λ2,θ12,h,k1)\nand row 2 purely from site-2 lattice values {Q1(θ2+rh)}_{r=0}^{λ2} (coefficients on k2). Since\nO[k1,k2]=Σ_{s,t}M[s,t](k1,k2)W[s,t] with W[s,t] (Section K's wave-function factorization) forming a\nbasis-independent coordinatization of the lattice-value data, the ansatz is EXACTLY equivalent to:\nthe (λ1+1)x(λ2+1) matrix M(k1,k2) has rank <=2 for every (k1,k2) — a 2x2 determinant is, by\ndefinition, a signed sum of exactly 2 rank-1 outer products u_i(k1)⊗v_i(k2).\n\nGATE 1 RESULT: rank<=2 is FALSE. The generic rank of M(k1,k2) is exactly min(λ1+1,λ2+1), i.e. FULL\nrank, not bounded by 2, for every representation pair with min(λ1,λ2)>=2 checked:\n  - Rep (2,2) [in the standard 6-rep sweep]: Det[M(k1,k2)] computed as an EXACT symbolic polynomial\n    (Cell 158) — (213003/7225)·k2^3·(k1-k2)^2·(17k1+46k2), a genuine nonzero degree-6 polynomial in\n    (k1,k2), not identically zero (rank drops to <=2 only on the measure-zero locus k2=0, k1=k2, or\n    17k1+46k2=0 — never \"everywhere\" as the ansatz requires). Confirmed at 4 independent rational\n    sample points, all giving rank exactly 3 (Cell 157), and independently cross-validated: the\n    M-based reconstruction Σ_{s,t}M[s,t]W[s,t] matches the known O2rot exactly at a sample point\n    (Cell 158's companion check), ruling out a bug in the M-matrix construction itself.\n  - Rep (2,3) [outside the standard sweep, checked for due diligence — full TauEigensystem/QSolve\n    machinery computed fresh for this rep]: a 3x3 minor of the 3x4 matrix M is nonzero\n    (19563970545/1405696), so rank>=3 there too (Cell 159).\n  - Every rep pair in the standard sweep with min(λ1,λ2)=1 (i.e. (1,1),(2,1),(1,2),(3,1),(1,3)) is\n    NOT a genuine test: since M is (λ1+1)x(λ2+1) with min(λ1+1,λ2+1)=2 there, rank<=2 holds\n    TRIVIALLY (it's the maximum possible rank for a matrix of that shape) regardless of whether\n    Paul's ansatz is true — these cases carry no information either way.\n\nCONCLUSION: within the standard sweep, the ONLY genuine test of Paul's rank-<=2 hypothesis is\nrep (2,2), and it fails there with generic rank exactly 3 = min(λ1+1,λ2+1); the (2,3) check shows\nthe same pattern (generic rank = min(λ1+1,λ2+1), not capped at 2) for a second, independent rep\npair with min(λ1,λ2)>=2. The natural reading: a FIXED-SIZE 2x2 determinant cannot represent\nO[k1,k2] for any representation with min(λ1,λ2)>=2 — the minimal determinant size needed grows\nwith min(λ1,λ2)+1, i.e. an r-term/r x r generalization would need r=min(λ1,λ2)+1, not the fixed\nr=2 Paul's ansatz specifies. Whether such a REP-SIZE-DEPENDENT determinant exists in closed form\n(row 1 built from λ1+1 site-1 values with min(λ1+1,λ2+1) rows worth of coefficient freedom, etc.)\nis a different, larger question not addressed here — reported as a precise gate-failure rather than\npursued further, per instruction.*)",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "(*Section M — Paul's single-tower ansatz. O[p,r] := (⟨x0[λ1]|e^{pE21}⊗⟨x0[λ2]|e^{rE21}).Psi[M,n]\n= O2rot[λ1,λ2][M,n][-p,-r] (O2rot used e^{-k1E21},e^{-k2E21}, so p=-k1,r=-k2). Target: state-\nindependent c_s(p,r;λ1,λ2) with O[p,r] = Σ_{s=0}^S c_s · Q1(θ1+sh)/Q1(θ1), a SINGLE site-1-tower\nsum. Method: exact linear algebra — the \"measurement matrix\" columns Q1(θ1+sh)/Q1(θ1) (s=0..S) are\nINDEPENDENT of (p,r) (built once per rep from Q1 alone), so for each (p,r) sample solve\nXc=b, X=measurement matrix (41-or-fewer-states x (S+1)), b=O[p,r] per state. Start S=λ1+λ2 per\ninstructions; escalate through the specified variant list only if inconsistent. Paul states this\nrepresentation is known to exist — a failed first solve means widen the ansatz, not conclude\nfalsity.*)",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(*O[p,r] and the site-1-tower measurement matrix (S=λ1+λ2 to start).*)\nClearAll[Opr,towerMat];\nOpr[λ1_,λ2_][M_,n_][p_,r_] := O2rot[λ1,λ2][M,n][-p,-r];\ntowerMat[λ1_,λ2_][S_] := Table[\n  Q1[λ1,λ2][st[[1]],st[[2]]][θ1+s h] / Q1[λ1,λ2][st[[1]],st[[2]]][θ1]\n,{st,statesOf[λ1,λ2]},{s,0,S}];\n(*rep (2,1): S=λ1+λ2=3, matrix is 6 states x 4 unknowns — overdetermined by 2.*)\nmat21 = towerMat[2,1][3];\n{\"towerMat dims (rep (2,1), S=3)\", Dimensions[mat21], \"MatrixRank\", MatrixRank[mat21]}",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
       "data": "<div class=\"wl-output-block\"><div class=\"wl-output-header\" style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;width:100%;min-height:22px;\" data-session-epoch=\"941596\" data-output-id=\"1108\" data-out-n=\"577\" data-sub-idx=\"6\" data-output-format=\"WLLatex\" data-output-is-graphics=\"0\" data-cell-idx=\"161\" data-sub-start=\"8\" data-sub-end=\"8\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;color:#888;margin-right:8px;\">Out[577]=</span></div><div class=\"wl-output-content\"><div class=\"vscode-wolfram-wllatex-prerendered wl-lb-pending\" data-lb-id=\"lb-mrqq09c8-bhnrsd3\" data-page-width-em=\"21\" data-latex-b64=\"XGxlZnRce1x0ZXh0e3Rvd2VyTWF0IGRpbXMgKHJlcCAoMiwxKSwgUz0zKX0sXGxlZnRcezYsNFxyaWdodFx9LFx0ZXh0e01hdHJpeFJhbmt9LDRccmlnaHRcfQ==\" style=\"opacity:0.65;transition:opacity 0.35s\"><div class=\"wl-lb-content\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">{</span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">towerMat dims (rep (2,1), S=3)</span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">{</span><span class=\"mord\">6</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">4</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">}</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">MatrixRank</span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">4</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">}</span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div></div></div>",
       "mime": "x-application/wolfram-language-html"
      },
      {
       "data": "Out[577]= \\left\\{\\text{towerMat dims (rep (2,1), S=3)},\\left\\{6,4\\right\\},\\text{MatrixRank},4\\right\\}",
       "mime": "text/plain"
      }
     ],
     "id": "8d456f7d-59bb-4329-a084-80350d3cde22"
    }
   ],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(*Solve for c_s at a sample (p,r), rep (2,1), S=λ1+λ2=3: b=O[p,r] per state, X=towerMat, exact\n  rational (p,r) for exact arithmetic.*)\nClearAll[rhsVec,solveTower];\nrhsVec[λ1_,λ2_][p_,r_] := Table[Opr[λ1,λ2][st[[1]],st[[2]]][p,r], {st,statesOf[λ1,λ2]}];\nsolveTower[λ1_,λ2_][S_][p_,r_] := Module[{Xm,bv,csol,resid},\n  Xm = towerMat[λ1,λ2][S];\n  bv = N[rhsVec[λ1,λ2][p,r],40];\n  csol = LeastSquares[Xm, bv];\n  resid = Max[Abs[Xm.csol - bv]];\n  {csol, resid}\n];\n{c21test, resid21test} = solveTower[2,1][3][7/3,5/2];\n{\"c_s (rep (2,1), S=3, p=7/3,r=5/2)\", Chop[c21test,10^-15], \"max residual\", resid21test}",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
       "data": "<div class=\"wl-output-block\"><div class=\"wl-output-header\" style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;width:100%;min-height:22px;\" data-session-epoch=\"941596\" data-output-id=\"1109\" data-out-n=\"582\" data-sub-idx=\"5\" data-output-format=\"WLLatex\" data-output-is-graphics=\"0\" data-cell-idx=\"162\" data-sub-start=\"12\" data-sub-end=\"12\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;color:#888;margin-right:8px;\">Out[582]=</span></div><div class=\"wl-output-content\"><div class=\"vscode-wolfram-wllatex-prerendered wl-lb-pending\" data-lb-id=\"lb-mrqq09qk-is5hi09\" data-page-width-em=\"21\" data-latex-b64=\"\" style=\"opacity:0.65;transition:opacity 0.35s\"><div class=\"wl-lb-content\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.2em;vertical-align:-0.35em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\"><span class=\"delimsizing size1\">{</span></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">c_s (rep (2,1), S=3, p=7/3,r=5/2)</span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">{</span><span class=\"mord\">13.7688078414687182186600</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">2.10326272230760132765845</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathrm\">i</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">−</span><span class=\"mord\">3.12167136931824065325212</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">18.8662496625125701186869</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathrm\">i</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">−</span><span class=\"mord\">7.51900595437450423013552</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">−</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">10.1245361864155291062487</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathrm\">i</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">3.80567731087062145228106</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">−</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0.708676905117290761157203</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathrm\">i</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">}</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">max residual</span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">27.6845440371648442360677</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\"><span class=\"delimsizing size1\">}</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div></div></div>",
